claim.claim-text:
1. A track link assembly comprising: 
a first pair of track links having an outer boss and an inner boss defined therein; 
a second pair of track links having an outer boss and an inner boss defined therein; 
a bushing having ends pressed into the inner boss of the second track links; 
a solid track pin positioned within the bushing, swaged to the outer boss of the first track links; 
a pair of thrust rings interposed between the ends of the bushing and the outer boss of the first track links; and 
a pair of seal assemblies each positioned adjacent one of the thrust rings and interposed between the ends of the bushing and the outer boss of the first track links.

6. A method of assembling a track link assembly comprising the steps of: 
positioning a thrust ring and seal assembly into a cavity adjacent to an outer boss of a first track link; 
pressing an end of a bushing into an inner boss of a second track link; 
lubricating a track pin; 
inserting the track pin through the bushing, outer boss and outer boss of the first track links; and 
swaging an end of the track pin to the outer boss of the first track links.
